history.content:
Hi! We are looking for qualified students to become academic interns for Spring 2020. Becoming an academic intern is a great way to solidify your understanding of DS100 material, help the next batch of students achieve mastery, and become part of the DS100 course staff. 

 

Please fill out this non-binding interest form (by Friday 1/10 at 11:59PM) if you're interested in becoming an Academic Intern for DS100 during the Spring 2020 semester!  Please do this even if you have submitted a UGSI/Reader application.

 

Details about the position are included in the form -- please read the form carefully before filling it out. 

 

Log in with your @berkeley.edu account to see the form.

 

We appreciate your interest and look forward to reading your application!
